parameters.name: Prefer
parameters.description: The server behavior requested by the client. Use 'respond-async' to execute the request asynchronously. If the request is executed asynchronously, 'Preference-applied: respond-async' is returned in the response.

parameters.name: X-NetSuite-Idempotency-Key
parameters.description: A user-defined unique idempotency key that is applied to every asynchronous requests to ensure that the request is executed only once. Only one request can be executed with every unique idempotency key. Use UUID in string format as defined by RFC 4122. If the request is executed synchronously, this value is ignored.

parameters.name: q
parameters.description: The search query that is used to filter results.

parameters.name: limit
parameters.description: The limit used to specify the number of results on a single page.

parameters.name: offset
parameters.description: The offset used for selecting a specific page of results.

aliennumber.title: Alien Number
aliennumber.description: Enter the employee's alien number. This is required only if the employee's work status is Alien authorized to work. The alien number is located in Section 1 of the completed I-9 form.

birthdate.title: Birth Date
birthdate.description: Enter the employee's date of birth.

password.title: Password
password.description: The Password and Confirm Password fields are only available if you checked the Manually Assign or Change Password box. Enter a password for the employee. As you type, the characters are validated against the password policy criteria, and the results displayed. You must tell the employee the password you assigned. Do not send the password by email. When you assign a password manually, you should also check the Require Password Change on Next Login box. For more information, see the help topic Password Requirements and Policies in NetSuite.

approvallimit.title: Expense Approval Limit
approvallimit.description: In the Expense Approval Limit field, enter the maximum amount this employee is allowed to approve on an expense report when specified as an approver for another employee. Expenses that exceed this amount must be approved by another supervisor or approver with a sufficient approval limit.

issupportrep.title: Support Rep
issupportrep.description: Check this box to mark this employee as a support representative. Support representatives are listed in the assigned to dropdown list for case forms and in the support rep dropdown list for support territory assignments.

fax.title: Fax
fax.description: Enter a fax number for this record. You should enter the fax number exactly as it must be dialed. If a '1' is required to fax to this number, be sure to include it at the beginning of the number. The number you enter here automatically appears in the To Be Faxed field of transactions when you select this employee. To fax NetSuite forms, an administrator must first set up fax service at Setup > Company > Printing, Fax & Email Preferences.

dateCreated.title: Date Created
dateCreated.description: The date and time at which the Employee Record was created.

lastName.title: Last Name
lastName.description: Enter the employee's last name here. What you enter here automatically appears last in the Employee field. The first letter of what you enter here appears in the Initials field. This field is required for the Online Bill Pay feature.

socialsecuritynumber.title: Social Security Number
socialsecuritynumber.description: Enter this employee's social security number here in the following format: 123-45-6789.

phone.title: Phone
phone.description: Enter a phone number for your employee. This field is required for Online Bill Pay enabled employees.

phoneticName.title: Furigana
phoneticName.description: Enter the furigana character you want to use to sort this record.

requirePwdChange.title: Require Password Change On Next Login
requirePwdChange.description: Check this box to require this user to change their password on their next login to NetSuite. When the user next logs in, they see the Change Password page and cannot access other NetSuite pages until a new password is created and saved. Requiring this action protects your account from unauthorized access using generic passwords and prepares your account for an audit. The Require Password Change on Next Login box never displays as checked. When you check this box and save the record, an internal flag is set. When the password change occurs, the flag is cleared. If you later check the box again and save the record, the internal flag is reset to require another password change.

purchaseorderapprovallimit.title: Purchase Approval Limit
purchaseorderapprovallimit.description: In the Purchase Approval Limit field, enter the maximum amount an employee is allowed to approve on a purchase request when specified as an approver for an employee.

purchaseorderlimit.title: Purchase Limit
purchaseorderlimit.description: In the Purchase Limit field, enter the amount this employee can purchase without approval from a supervisor or approver.

defaultAddress.title: Default Address
defaultAddress.description: The employee's address. You can enter this information on the Address subtab, and it will appear here.

isJobManager.title: Job Manager
isJobManager.description: Check this box to mark the employee as a Project Manager. The employee will be added to Project Manager dropdown list in Primary Information of the project record. (This field is enabled when employee is marked as Project Resource.)

password2.title: Confirm Password
password2.description: Re-enter the employee's password for verification. When you manually assign a password, you need to tell the employee the login information. Do not send the password by email.

email.title: Email
email.description: Enter your employee's email address. If you allow your employees to track time or enter expense reports online, this will become part of their access codes.

visaexpdate.title: Visa Expiration Date
visaexpdate.description: Enter the expiration date of the employee's visa. This information can be obtained from the employee's passport.

issalesrep.title: Sales Rep
issalesrep.description: Check this box to mark this employee as a sales representative. Sales representatives are listed in the sales rep dropdown list for sales order forms and for sales territory assignments.

expenselimit.title: Expense Limit
expenselimit.description: In the Expense Limit field, enter the amount this employee can expense without approval from a supervisor or approver.

autoName.title: Auto
autoName.description: Clear this box to manually enter an ID for this record. If you leave this box checked, NetSuite assigns an ID for this record based on your settings at Setup > Company > Auto-Generated Numbers.

externalId.title: External ID
externalId.description: Returns the employee's external ID, if one is assigned.

entityId.title: Entity ID
entityId.description: If the Auto box is not checked, manually enter an ID for this record. If the Auto box is checked, NetSuite assigns an ID for this record based on your settings at Setup > Company > Auto-Generated Numbers.

releasedate.title: Termination/Release Date
releasedate.description: Enter this person's last date of employment.

hireDate.title: Hire Date
hireDate.description: Enter the date this employee was hired.

isJobResource.title: Job Resource
isJobResource.description: Check this box to enable this employee to be added as a resource on projects and tasks.

targetUtilization.title: Target Utilization
targetUtilization.description: Select the required utilization for this resource.

mobilePhone.title: Mobile Phone
mobilePhone.description: Enter this employee's mobile or cell phone number here.

initials.title: Initials
initials.description: NetSuite automatically completes this field as you enter first, middle and last names. If you want to make changes to an employee's initials, enter up to three letters in this field.

salutation.title: Mr./Ms...
salutation.description: Enter the employee's salutation, such as Mr. or Ms., here.

lastReviewDate.title: Last Review Date
lastReviewDate.description: Enter the date of this person's last salary evaluation.

isInactive.title: Is Inactive
isInactive.description: Check this box to inactivate this employee record. Inactivated records no longer appear in lists or as choices anywhere in your account. To view inactivated employee records or reactivate them, go to Lists > Employees > Employees, and check the Show Inactives box.

firstName.title: First Name
firstName.description: Enter the employee's first name here. What you enter here automatically appears first in the Employee field. The first letter of what you enter here appears in the Initials field. This field is required for the Online Bill Pay feature.

jobdescription.title: Job Description
jobdescription.description: Enter a description of the duties related to the job this person currently performs.

homePhone.title: Home Phone
homePhone.description: Enter this employee's home phone number here.

i9verified.title: I-9 Verified
i9verified.description: Check this box if the employee has completed an I-9 form.

title.title: Job Title
title.description: Enter this employee's official job title here.

laborCost.title: Labor Cost
laborCost.description: Enter the employee's hourly overhead labor rate. This rate is used to calculate the estimated cost of jobs this employee works on.

giveAccess.title: Login Access
giveAccess.description: Check this box to give your employee access to NetSuite. Then, assign a role to customize the level of access. You can assign multiple roles. To let your employee track time and enter expense reports, select the Employee Center role.

nextReviewDate.title: Next Review Date
nextReviewDate.description: Enter the date of this person's next salary evaluation.

comments.title: Notes
comments.description: Enter other information you want to track for this employee.

accountNumber.title: Account
accountNumber.description: If you, your payroll service, or other benefits provider assigns account numbers to your employees, enter that account number here. This field is required for the Online Bill Pay feature.

authworkdate.title: Work Authorization Expiry Date
authworkdate.description: Enter the date through which the employee is authorized to work until. This is required only if the employee's work status is Alien authorized to work. This date is located in Section 1 of the completed I-9 form.

lastModifiedDate.title: Last Modified Date
lastModifiedDate.description: Returns the date on which the employee record was last modified.

middleName.title: Middle Name
middleName.description: Enter a middle name or initial here. What you enter here automatically appears second in the Employee field. The first letter of what you enter here appears in the Initials field. Enter up to 25 characters in this field.

concurrentwebservicesuser.title: Concurrent Web Services User
concurrentwebservicesuser.description: A user type that allows concurrent web services access into NetSuite. Check this box to allow a user to have standard UI login access plus up to ten concurrent web services sessions.

officePhone.title: Office Phone
officePhone.description: Enter this employee's office phone number here.

sendEmail.title: Send New Access Notification Email
sendEmail.description: Check this box to send an automatic email notifying this employee of access privileges to NetSuite. The standard NetSuite email message also contains a link to let the user create a password. If you do not check this box, you must check the Manually Assign or Change Password box. You must create the password, and tell the user the password, and when and how to log in. For security reasons, do not send the password by email.

type.title: Type
type.description: A URI reference to the documentation about the problem type.

title.title: Title
title.description: A human-readable description of the problem type.

status.title: Status
status.description: The HTTP status code generated by the server the request originates from.

o:errorDetails.description: An array containing one or more problem types.

detail.title: Detail
detail.description: A detailed, human-readable description of the problem occurrence.

o:errorPath.title: Error Path
o:errorPath.description: The JSON path that indicates where the problem occurs within the request body.

o:errorUrl.title: Error URL
o:errorUrl.description: The URI of the first element in the request URL where the problem occurs.

o:errorHeader.title: Error Header
o:errorHeader.description: The name of the HTTP header where the problem occurs.

o:errorQueryParam.title: Error Query Parameter
o:errorQueryParam.description: The name of the query parameter where the problem occurs.

o:errorCode.title: Error Code
o:errorCode.description: The application-specific error code. Similar problem types are grouped together.

items.title: Items
items.description: An array field that represents a collection of elements, for example, sublist lines, multiselect items, or search results.
